\begin_layout Standard
I am writing to apply to Pacific Northwest National Laboratory for the Post
 Doctorate RA in Nuclear Monitoring.
 The research I will be presenting for my upcoming PhD defense is on the
 use of novel neutron detectors - Tensioned Metastable Fluid Detectors -
 in passive and active interrogation for special nuclear material interdiction.
 I design the detectors, and write automation firmware and control software,
 with the detectors recently winning the best demo award at the 2016 IEEE
 Sensors conference.
 I have also received awards for my data analysis and simulation work (done
 using C++, Python, Matlab, Fortran, MCNP, and COMSOL), particularly the
 best paper at the 2016 American Nuclear Society Winter Meeting for my paper
 analyzing our detection methodology for highly enriched uranium and the
 2017 Innovations in Nuclear Technology R&D Award for the same methodology.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the work on these methods, I've developed some of the skills that the
 call for Nuclear Monitoring Post-Doc references.
 I've been required to perform gamma-ray spectroscopy - most recently for
 enrichment verification of unknown samples of uranium dioxide with inclusions
 and without enrichment standards to compare against.
 I've also had to creatively use MCNP/MCNP-Polimi on many diverse problems
 in our detection context - from photoneutron production and subsequent
 detection in a clinical bremsstrahlung accelerator source to the directionally
 dependent spectra and its effect on our detector in a 
